def process(state,  gdf,df = cov19df):
    stateDf1 = df[df["Province_State"] == state]
    stateDf1.rename(columns = {"Admin2": "name"}, inplace = True)
    stateDf = stateDf1.merge(gdf, how = "inner", on = "name", indicator = False)
    meltedDf = pd.melt(stateDf,id_vars='name', value_vars = list(stateDf.columns[12:332].values),
        var_name = 'date', value_name = 'deaths')
    meltedDf['datetime'] = meltedDf.apply(lambda x: 
        datetime.strptime(x['date'], '%m/%d/%y'), axis = 1)
    county_count = len(meltedDf['name'].unique())
    stateDeaths = meltedDf[(-1*county_count):]['deaths'].sum()
    stateFinal = meltedDf[-county_count:].copy()
    #meltedDf['deathsNormalized'] = meltedDf.apply(lambda 
    #    x:(x['deaths']*stateDeaths)/(stateFinal[stateFinal['name'] 
    #    == x['name']]['deaths'].values[0]), axis = 1)
  #  meltedDf['alpha'] = meltedDf.apply(lambda x: stateFinal[stateFinal['name']
  #      == x['name']]['deaths'].values[0]/stateDeaths, axis =1)
 #   alpha_normalized = scaler.fit_transform(meltedDf['alpha'].values.reshape(-1,1))
 #   meltedDf['alpha'] = alpha_normalized
    return meltedDf

def countyPlot(srcDf,state,color):
    f = bkplt.figure(plot_width = 800, plot_height = 800, x_axis_type = 'datetime', title = state)
    top5 = srcDf.sort_values(by = "deaths")['name'].unique()[-5:]
    for s in srcDf['name'].unique():
        if( s in top5 ):
            continue
        df = srcDf[srcDf['name'] == s]
      #  alpha = df.iloc[0]['alpha']
        alpha = 1
        f.line(df['datetime'], df['deaths'], alpha = alpha, color = color, line_width = 3)
    for s in top5:
        df = srcDf[srcDf['name'] == s]
        #alpha = df.iloc[0]['alpha']
        alpha = 1
        p = f.line(df['datetime'], df['deaths'], alpha = alpha, color = color,
        muted_alpha=1, legend_label= s, muted_line_width = 6)
    f.legend.location = "top_left"
    f.legend.title = "Top 5 "+state+" Counties"
    f.legend.click_policy="mute"
    return f
bkplt.show(row(countyPlot(process("Texas",  txGdf), "Texas", "blue"),
         countyPlot(process("North Carolina",  ncGdf), "North Carolina", "green")))
